description: Dimensions: L 113mm; We 42.2mm; Wbt 20mm; Bst 29.5mm; Blp 8.3mm; Tsep 13.3mm,Typology: pointed fg. crests - flattened ends, angular top edge to stop, rounded bev. below, rounded original below st; sep. angles sl. rounded or dimpled; sl. skew in fg. to sep.,Manufacture: parts of cg. fl. stumps evid.; some lipping on side from forging of fg. ends; marked blade tip hollows; hammer rippling over much of blade; odd pmks on blade - possible damage,Condition: edge totally blunted - at least partly recent - dull golden brown; butt top sim. colour - prob. recent hammering; gold flecks along fg. crests etc.,Attached Material: fawn and light ruddy brown soil traces

surface: Gold brown to dark brown patina; granular textured areas of light green surface; virtually no pocking, but flaking at edge; slight silveryness on one blade face crests rubbed to smooth dull gold - but not damaged
description: Dimensions: L 135mm; We 35.7mm; Wbt 18.4mm; Bst 29.9; Blp 8.3mm; T sep 13.6mm; Tbt 4.3mm,Typology: fg. and st. crests rounded; some fg. end flattened; sep. end rounded rect.; slight twist - sep. to blade edge.,Manufacture: 2 or 3 cavities penetrating butt end, small hollow in one blade side - cg. defects; some irreg. in fg. tops - mainly cg. features; hammer rippling on lower blade; cg. fl. stumps on central part only,Condition: butt end - broken surface; blade edge all blunt - prob. just corr. damage.,Attached Material: fawn to light brown soil traces

surface: Olive brown patina, much speckled and mini-pocked to light-green dusty surface.
description: Dimensions: L 131mm; We 36mm; Wbt21mm; Bst 30.8mm; Blp 7.9mm; T sep 14mm; Tbt 6mm,Typology: intact fg. crests narrow, rounded; slight depression in one butt face - deliberate feature?; stop crest with fairly crisp bev. on upper edge, rounded one lower; rect. sep. end - angles qt. crisp; central part of two opposite blade angles facetted - prob. damaged.,Manufacture: slight skew on fg. and blade - slight valve dislocation marked discontinuity in loop; traces of cg. fl on central sides with slight step - removed elsewhere; porosity holes in one sep. end; depression in one blade face - cg. flaw? - has a fairly regular 'pear' shape; slight tendency to blade tip hollows; possible hints of rippling on lower blade; very slight depression in opp. face; hairline crack across blade edge - possibly forging crack - or p. crazing? notch in one fg.-cg. flaw,Condition: edge totally blunt - corr. chipping; butt top broken surface; little corrosion damage to crest of fgs and sls.,Attached Material: light brown soil adhering
remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink: 567/8; printed small square s/o label: 8,printed black ink: 567

surface: dark greeny-brown patina; much speckled to light green
description: Dimensions: L 134mm; We 36.7mm; Wbt 17.5mm; Bst 31.3mm; Blp 8.5mm; Tbt 5.8mm (approx); T sep 12.4mm,Typology: irregular longt. furrow down either sep.,Manufacture: stump of cg. fl. on fg. sides only - removed butt and blade; large cavity in blade fave and reverse se. - cg. defects - nick in lp. prob. also; some diffuse hammer marks; low on blade,Condition: broken surface at butt end; edge blunt - probably all lost by corrosion; stop and fg. crests very little damage,Attached Material: fawn to light brown soil traces
remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink 567/7,small square s/o label: 7

remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink: 567/6,small square label s/o black ink 6 = printed

remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink: 567/5; black ink: 567 printed

surface: Mainly gold to dark brown patina: little scattered pocking to pale green; dark chocolate brown at some breaks

remarks: Labels/Markings: white ink 567; black ink 567/4; black ink printed 567

surface: Black to green-brown patina; localised patches of brighter green speckled texture surface; pocking and flaking, mainly close to blade edge, to light green dusty surface; chipping at edge also revealing dark brown smooth surface.
description: Dimensions: L 151.3mm; Wbl.e 35.6mm; Wbt 19.5mm; max B bt 5.5mm; T sep 14.5mm; B st. 31.7mm; Blp 10.2mm,Typology: crisp body angles to butt end, but each with facet, just below end; fg. crests mainly rounded to flat and undulating; underside of st. bevelled - reverse one more regular; constriction at top of blade not defined by neat side bevels; blade angles crisp; septum angles fairly crisp, corners little rounded, end little bowed; both septums offset to right at bottom,Manufacture: low fairly narrow stump of cg. fl. on loop - rounded with some battering; above loop and on central part of reverse side low broad flat-topped cg. fl with hammer marks, but no  sign lpg.; fully removed elsewhere on sides, where some suggestion of hammer marks, also on lower blade; very slight hollows immediately beneath stops on faces - probably cg. flaws; some irregularity on fg. insides - as cast,Condition: butt end a broken surface - untampered with; blade edge more or less intact, but not sharp, possibly due to det.; band of diagonal grmks. up on blade face - pres. modern but no diff. colour,Attached Material: butt soil traces, especially on butt end and under lp.
remarks: Recognised in 1979 as a hafted axe, wrongly marked '568'; its identification as from the South Farm Road hoard, indicated by the old B.A.C. and, is verified by the early published photograph (a),Labels/Markings: white ink 568 - incorrect (in 1979)

surface: Dark green patina; parts flaking to pale greens, especially at edge; measure of granular textured dull green
description: Dimensions: L 132.2mm; EWe 46.0mm; Wbt 24.5mm; Bst 34.0mm; Blp 8.6mm; T sep 15.2mm; Tbb 5.7 mm (approx),Typology: five irregularly spaced ribs - 2 outer ones very thing - flatten at bases and merge out; angular square-ended septum; blade cast with a flare below decoration; rounded fg. crests - medium broad; inner edge of stop qt. angular bevelled underside; bev. on septum across fg. ends,Manufacture: blade faces cast or forged into 4 longitudinal facets - few individual hammer marks possibly discernible; broad stumps of cg. fl. - some practically or totally removed - hammer marks; hammer flattening of fg. ends; 2 valves of mould dislocated; loop asymmetric., septums different lengths;  asymmetric fg. section; small proj. on one side - cg. defect?; much of butt-end smoothed.,Condition: virtually all of edge lost - chipped to pale green and dark chocolate brown; fgs and sts mainly undamaged,Attached Material: light orangey-brown soil traces in many places
remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink 567/2; black ink printed: 567

surface: Milky green to gold - brown mottled patina; scattered minor pocking to pale green surface
description: Dimensions: L 164.3mm; We 38.2mm; Wbt 22.3mm; Bst. 37mm; Blp 9.3mm; T sep 16.6mm; Tbt 7.5mm,Typology: five short ribs on either face, outer ones slightly thinner - terminals emphasised by  forged bev.; angular blade edges; rounded st. and fg. crests - latter very narrow; slight bowing to butt faces,Manufacture: some fg. ends clipped by hammering; cg. fl. remains only on flange sides only - totally removed from butt and blade sides - some hammer marks here; part of cg. fl. quite sharp - untrimmed; small irregular bulbous mouldings on fg. and sl - defects; slight hammermark damage much of blade, with qt. distinct; edge bev. low down; cavities in one septum end - cg. flaws,Condition: butt top - broken surface - probably in manufacturing; edge basically in tact, blunted from patina flaking; crests on one face - corrosion chipped.,Attached Material: Chalky to fawn  matrix mainly in hollows
remarks: Labels/Markings: black ink: 567/1; black ink printed: 567 - [foded?]

collection: Worthing Museum,54/439,Presented 14 Aug. 1954 by Mr. Nebley, 42 Chester Avenue, Worthing
surface: Dark browny green patina; much covered with crumb-textured green corrosion layer
description: Dimensions: L 169mm; We 70.5mm; Bfg. 26.6mm; min B st. 21.3mm; max T sep 8.4mm,Typology: septum floor slightly dished, with quite angular corners and tendency for pointed end especially on reverse; bt. end slightly thick - but rounded, not neat; flattened stop crests and parts of fgs; shield-shaped depression - no encircling rib, vertical ridge-and-furrows inside - 4 or 5, some vague,Manufacture: alight traces only of cg. fl - well removed; edge bev. - line diffuse due to corrosion? very slight blade tip hollows; srmks and pmks on sides - diagonal and longitudinal - anc. mainly; pore hole low in one fg.; odd longit pmks in septum,Condition: edge blunt but intact - partly anc. blunting partly corrosion damage; odd gold flecks on corners, etc. - mod. interference; little corrosion damage at butt perhaps,Attached Material: patches of fawn soil adhering
remarks: Circumstances: "During August 1954, Mr. J. Webley unearthed a type B palstave at Lyon's Farm Nurseries on the Upper Brighton Road. An inspection of the site revealed no further finds." (a),Labels/Markings: white ink: 54.439

surface: Dark brown shiny patina; little speckling of fir green textured surface
description: Dimensions: L 122.8mm; EWe 37.6mm; Wbt 20.3mm; Bst 29.5mm; Blp. 8.2mm; T sep 14.3mm; Tbt 7.8mm,Typology: narrow rounded fg. crests; tendency for flattened stop crests with angular upper edge and more rounded lower one, fairly crisp septum angles,Manufacture: stumps of cg. fl. on both sides - broad in parts - possibly from forging - above loop double flash! - Right hand one more prominent; rough surface under and around loop - probably cg. flaw - as are two nicks in one fg.; curved bev. on one blade face with hammer marks belowe - not very evidence on reverse slight blade tip hollows; sudden thinning of septum at butt-original probably-butt end forged causing little lipping - anc.,Condition: intact part of blade edge,slight blunted - probably recent, other half broken off in ant.; little of blunt end retains broken surface. from snapping jet.,Attached Material: traces of fawn soil

site: England, west sussex,worthing,chatham road,40 acres brickfield
surface: Palid green to silvery surfaces, much rubbed etc. to brown and gold.
description: Dimensions: EL 47.5mm; W (at upper break) 24mm; EBst 29.8mm; Blp 11mm; Tsep 15.7mm,Typology: longt. furrow in either septum becomes deeper depression at bottom end; off-centered rib running up one septum end; 3 ribs on one face - possibly converging - almost totally removed from reverse face - traces evident; blade angles probably quite crisp before mutilation.,Manufacture: stumps of cg. fl. - including large lump in upper loop angle; add small pits in septums may be cg. defect,Condition: central body fragment - both breaks ancient; stop and fg. crests very battered front fgs and both stops possibly not reduced much - reverse fgs possibly more lost; reverse blade face, outer loop surface, and much of reverse side, mutilated by gouging and filing - dark brown and gold,Attached Material: slight traces of light brown soil; three white grits (?) embedded

surface: Dark brown patina, mottled/rubbed to green in places; few scattered pocks to pale green, and flaking mainly at edge, to pale green and chocolate brown.
description: Dimension: L 123.5 mm; We 39mm; Wbt 21.2mm; Bst 28.4mm; Blp 7.7mm; T sep 12.8mm; Tbt 4.0mm (approx),Typology: rounded fg. and stop crests, lump in other; approx rect. septum end; rather asym.  loop form,Manufacture: parts of cg. fl. stump, large and irregular - especially at top with lipping - much removed on blade sides; undulating furrow longt. stem one septum and depression in reverse - flow flaws? - also small notches in fg.?; well curved and bev. with hammer marks  - tending to split into 3 facets; blade tip hollow; little porosity in butt-end, and in one septum end.,Condition: butt end broken surface; edge all blunt - probably from corrosion.,Attached Material: light brown to fawn soil in a number of places.

surface: Dark brown/olive mottled patina; small patches of pocking.speckling to light green.

description: Dimensions: L 135.4mm; We 32mm; B st 29.2mm; max T sep 14mm,Typology: blade angles insp., both faces and sides bowed; rounded fg. and stop crests, diffuse arched devel across septum at fg. ends; crisp septum angles,Manufacture: 2 grooves on underside of stop - cg. flaws; partial remains of thin cg. fl. sides - qt. markedly off-centre; totally removed on blade landing to facets; diffuse bevel to to blade edge; cavity in reverse face of butt, with longt. furrow below - both cg. defects; some undulation of septum floor; 2 small hollows in reverse side - cg. flaws; score along one septum - recent dam?,Condition: edge mainly intact and sharp - few odd chips of patina removed; lp. breaks probably recent - purply brown colour; butt very uneven - one corner recently chipped, rest original break or damage?; also much of one fg.,Attached Material: fawn soil traces

surface: Dull brown/gold patina; few scattered pocks to light green dry surface.

Depression in rev. butt face at top - cg. feature; pit in sim. position on face - possiblly anc.; little hammer rippling on lower blade face,Condition: edge virtually intact and sharp - possible minimal mod. interference; some very small dents, etc.; hairline fracture particularly to and very close to edge; grmks at edge probably recent - assoc. with dull gold patch;,Attached Material: patches embedded with light brown and fawn matrix

site: England, west sussex,worthing,chatham road,40 acres brickfield

site: England, west sussex,worthing,chatham road,40 acres brickfield

site: England, west sussex,worthing,chatham road,40 acres brickfield
surface: Fine deep green patina; large parts of reverse face and sides pocking to light green, dry surface, or flaked at crests, etc.
description: Dimensions: EL 108.0mm; EWe 43.0mm; EBfg 23.6mm; T sep 7.0mm; Bst 22.7mm,Typology: one st. crest dipped, other humped - probably original; broad midrib begins at lower level than stop; remains of side-fgs; remnants of shoulder humps on sides; fgs probably originally leaf-shaped; septum broad 'U' section;,Manufacture: row of pits only to suggest eg. fl.; number of deep cavities of small bore - probably porosity; blade extensively ? forged, truncating ribs - mainly smooth, little undulating but no clear hammer marks; some fine long t. strations in septum may be anc.; shorter "brush" scmks and other long t ones look post p, but not necessarily recent,Condition: edge very blunt - possibly some medn. interf. - dark brown rubbed; one corner of butt -broken surface-probably anc., rest rubbed brown - originally broken? fg crests well ribbed - possibly not much lost; some cut facets on blade edges - recent,Attached material: very few small traces of light brown soil.

description: Dimensions: EL 145.2mm; EWe 28.3 mm; B st 28.3mm; Tsep 7.5mm,Typology: stop possibly curved, with rounded corners with flanges; slight constriction at top of blade which has straight flared sides below; trident decoration evident on one face - upper forked part almost in form of tapered rib with midridge - lower small rib; less pronounced decoration on reverse face; possibly little emphasised blade sides; in profile; probably sloped stop underside; projection from side suggest original loop,Condition: all edges damaged by corrosion - very poor general condition; part of one flange - adj. to stop possible virtually intact.,Attached Material: Yellow soil traces attached

Some dimples/ripples on blade faces may be from casting - others possibly pmks; slight porosity at main fracture main break ancient,Attached Material: Yellow - fawn soil traces
